From: Nickel Browser Team <team@nickel-browser.org>
Date: Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 02/10] nickel: user-agent — set Nickel product token

Keep the standard Chrome/Chromium UA format so websites don't break,
but add a Nickel product token so users can identify their browser.

Result:  Mozilla/5.0 (...) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko)
         Chrome/146.0.7680.177 Nickel/1.0 Safari/537.36

The Chrome version is preserved for maximum site compatibility.
---
 chrome/common/channel_info.cc | 10 +++++++++-
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/chrome/common/channel_info.cc b/chrome/common/channel_info.cc
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/chrome/common/channel_info.cc
+++ b/chrome/common/channel_info.cc
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
-// Copyright 2022 The Chromium Authors
+// Copyright 2022 The Chromium Authors; Nickel Browser modifications 2026
 // Use of this source code is governed by a BSD-style license that can be
 // found in the LICENSE file.
 
@@ -20,6 +20,14 @@ std::string GetChannelName(WithExtendedStable with_extended_stable) {
   return std::string();
 }
 
+#if defined(NICKEL_BROWSER)
+// Nickel Browser: append product token to user-agent string.
+// Called from content::BuildUserAgentFromProduct().
+std::string GetNickelProductToken() {
+  return "Nickel/1.0";
+}
+#endif  // defined(NICKEL_BROWSER)
+
 std::string GetChannelSuffixForDataDir() {
   return std::string();
 }
-- 
2.40.0
